  "original_title": "\u2018\u2018\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0dca\u0d85\u0d9f\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dab\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd0\u0dba 10\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba \u0db1\u0dd1\u2018\u2018",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"If coal runs out, there will be no electricity for 10 hours\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "If it is not possible to import the required amount of coal in the future, there will be a 10-hour power cut, said Mr. Patali Champika Ranawaka, the leader of the 43rd Division and Member of Parliament.",
        "Mr. Patali Champika Ranawaka mentioned that since coal can be unloaded only during a limited time, twenty five lakh tons of coal should be unloaded from the end of this month to next April, otherwise diesel power plants will have to be operated more and costs may be high.",
        "The councilor said that a cabinet paper has been submitted to import the required coal until 2025 in such a situation where it is not possible to import even the required amount of coal for a few months. Mr. Ranawaka said that a crisis has now arisen because coal was procured in a way that could not withstand the country's economic situation and dollar reserves, and said that if it continues to be done in an informal manner, it can have very dangerous results.",
        "The MP also said that the suspicion has arisen that the royal sons who cheated the Lanka Electricity Board of 49 crores by saying that they were sending rockets in the past are also getting their hands on oil."
      ],
